Applying Arrow’s Impossibility Theorem

Class Group Project (Brown University)

CSCI 1710: Logic for Systems is a course that explores using mathematical logic to reason about systems and discovering whether their behavior meets our expectations.

As a final project, my group of three decided to model a simple plurality and ranked-choice voting system, and demonstrated the satisfiability and validity of the three components of{" "} Arrow’s Impossibility Theorem {" "} in each of the modeled voting systems.
